The paper discusses the use of algorithms and statistical methods to learn the structure of belief networks from data, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with causal relationships and the use of directed acyclic graphs, which are topics in systems and control (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to handle situations where there are causally insufficient sets of variables, which is a topic in data mining (cs.DM).
